after nearly 36 years in business as the one-stop-shop and online resource for high-tech professionals across nine states and 31 stores, fry’s electronics, inc. has made the difficult decision to shut down its operations and close its business permanently as a result of changes in the retail industry and the challenges posed by the covid-19 pandemic. the company ceased regular operations and began the wind-down process on february 24, 2021. it is hoped that undertaking the wind-down through this orderly process will reduce costs, avoid additional liabilities, minimize the impact on our customers, vendors, landlords and associates, and maximize the value of the company’s assets for its creditors and other stakeholders.


on april 2, 2021, fry’s electronics, inc. entered into an assignment for the benefit of creditors and appointed frys (assignment for the benefit of creditors), llc as assignee of the fry’s assignment estate. the assignment is an insolvency proceeding that was commenced under california state law. as a result of the assignment, fry’s is no longer promoting, distributing, or selling any products. meanwhile, the assignee is in the process of selling the fry’s related assets. for any creditor or other interested party needing to file a proof of claim for outstanding invoices or other claims or for more information regarding the assignment, please click here: www.proofofclaims.com/frys/documents

if you have questions, please contact us using the following email addresses:

- for any creditor or other interested party needing to file a proof of claim for outstanding invoices or other claims or for more information regarding the assignment, please click here: www.proofofclaims.com/frys/documents

- performance service contracts will be honored for their full remaining term. to request service of your covered product, please call assurant at (800) 811-1745

- for consignment vendors needing to pick up their consignment inventory please email omnichannel@frys.com.

- for fry’s credit card holders with a balance due, you will continue to make your payments to first electronic bank on a monthly basis as before. follow this link www.fryscredit.com to pay your bill.


please understand if we are a bit slow to respond given the large volume of questions. the company appreciates your patience and support through this process.


sincerely,


fry’s electronics
